name: FIRST_LOCAL_VIDEO_FRAME
description: Occurs when the first local video frame is rendered.The SDK triggers this callback when the first local video frame is displayed/rendered on the local video view.

parameters.width: The width (px) of the first local video frame.

parameters.height: The height (px) of the first local video frame.

parameters.elapsed:
Time elapsed (ms) from the local user calling joinChannel until the SDK triggers this callback. If
                              you call startPreview before calling joinChannel, then this parameter is the time elapsed
                              from calling the startPreview method until the SDK
                              triggers this callback.
